<div id="banner">
	<h1>Several years ago an aunt</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Several years ago an aunt gave me several shares of Disney stock as a birthday present. Every year they mail us the annual report, along with a ticket to the shareholders meeting and a voting form. They allow you to <a href="http://www.proxyvote.com/">vote online</a> nowadays, and so I went out to fill out the ballot.<p /><p />It&#8217;s pretty easy to tell what to vote for: simply do the opposite of what Disney asks for. They want us to approve &#8220;the 2002 Executive Performance Plan&#8221; (<a href="http://purl.org/net/sbp/">Sean</a>: &#8220;All those in favour of giving ourselves a 10% pay raise&#8230;&#8221;), and vote against independent accountants, labor standards in China and theme park safety reporting.<p /><p /><a href="http://wired.com/wired/archive/10.02/">Everybody loves Disney</a>, right?</p>

<p class="posted">posted January 21, 2002 05:43 AM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_"></a>)  <a href="000128" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

